2
00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:10.780
That's Kaido's skin!

3
00:00:13.910 --> 00:00:17.250
<b>Prisoner
 Mining 
Camp


Udon</b>

4
00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:21.380
Remember your defeat!

5
00:00:27.450 --> 00:00:31.090
Remember how futile
brute strength proved to be!

6
00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:44.820
That steel slab looks like jelly!

7
00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:56.660
<b>Five Days

Until the Raid</b>

8
00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:56.660
Five days until the raid.

9
00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:16.100
One Piece

10
00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:16.100
Wano Arc

11
00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:44.270
<b>Enma</b>

12
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:48.190
This is Kin'emon speaking.

13
00:02:48.680 --> 00:02:52.990
The flyers you possess
have had their symbols changed.

14
00:02:52.990 --> 00:02:55.450
<b>Amigasa
 Village


Kuri</b>

15
00:02:53.320 --> 00:02:55.450
“Add two lines on the belly of the viper.”

16
00:02:56.820 --> 00:03:01.490
That was the message from Lord Yasuie!

17
00:03:06.470 --> 00:03:07.750
Two lines...

18
00:03:11.050 --> 00:03:12.870
Two lines?!

19
00:03:16.550 --> 00:03:19.010
<b>Weapons
Preparation
Team

Udon</b>

20
00:03:16.550 --> 00:03:18.510
I see!

21
00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:22.890
<b>Weapons
Transport
Team

Ringo</b>

22
00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:22.040
Lord Yasuie, you sly fox.

23
00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:24.270
Of course...

24
00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:28.900
<b>Yakuza
Command
Team

Kibi</b>

25
00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:26.830
That's it. Understood.

26
00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:31.650
Hey! Use your lower body strength more!

27
00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:41.490
<b>Ship
Maintenance
Team


Itachi Port

Kuri</b>

28
00:03:32.250 --> 00:03:35.900
If you don't, it won't make it on
the rough seas around Onigashima!

29
00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:37.560
– Yes, Boss!
– Yes, Boss!

30
00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:39.780
Come on, use your lower body!

31
00:03:37.560 --> 00:03:40.310
Two lines on the belly of the viper?

32
00:03:40.310 --> 00:03:41.490
Got it!

33
00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:44.160
I understand, Sir Kin'emon!

34
00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:46.620
Yes, I am glad that you do.

35
00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:52.250
Is that Kin'emon? We'll have
all these ships as good as new!

36
00:03:52.800 --> 00:03:56.590
We're super on it!

37
00:03:56.860 --> 00:04:00.220
– Leave it to us!
– We've got this!

38
00:04:00.220 --> 00:04:03.640
Tell everyone about the change in the symbol!

39
00:04:03.870 --> 00:04:05.450
Thank you.

40
00:04:06.210 --> 00:04:07.100
Incredible!

41
00:04:07.770 --> 00:04:13.070
Anyone from Wano will instantly figure out
the meaning of the additional lines!

42
00:04:13.070 --> 00:04:16.490
So... What does it mean?

43
00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:18.700
Two dashes on habu would spell...

44
00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:21.320
Babu?!

45
00:04:22.700 --> 00:04:27.710
You cannot decrypt the message if you do not
first know the names of Wano's ports.

46
00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:31.380
<b>Itachi
(Weasel) Port</b>

47
00:04:30.030 --> 00:04:31.380
Itachi Port.

48
00:04:33.130 --> 00:04:34.670
<b>Neko
(Cat) Port</b>
Neko Port.

49
00:04:34.670 --> 00:04:36.130
<b>Kaeru
(Frog) Port</b>
Kaeru Port.

50
00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:37.550
<b>Mogura
(Mole) Port</b>

51
00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:37.530
Mogura Port.

52
00:04:37.530 --> 00:04:39.010
Tokage Port.

53
00:04:37.550 --> 00:04:39.010
<b>Tokage
(Lizard) Port</b>

54
00:04:39.010 --> 00:04:41.840
<b>Habu
(Viper) Port</b>
And lastly, Habu Port.

55
00:04:42.250 --> 00:04:47.060
Every port in Wano has a name
that sounds like an animal.

56
00:04:47.510 --> 00:04:49.910
Initially, using the image of a viper,

57
00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:53.520
<b>Kaeru 
Port</b>
<b>Itachi 
Port</b>
<b>Mogura 
Port</b>
<b>Tokage
 Port</b>
<b>Habu
 Port</b>
<b>Neko 
Port</b>

58
00:04:49.910 --> 00:04:53.520
we implied that Habu Port is the rendezvous point.

