<b>Itachi 
Port</b>
<b>Mogura 
Port</b>
<b>Neko 
Port</b>

70
00:05:01.410 --> 00:05:03.960
Tokage Port is in Udon.

71
00:05:04.830 --> 00:05:09.160
By changing the rendezvous point
from Habu Port to Tokage Port,

72
00:05:09.160 --> 00:05:13.290
even the most clever of foes
will be unable to hinder our plan.

73
00:05:13.830 --> 00:05:15.250
The noble Yasuie...

74
00:05:16.050 --> 00:05:21.510
must have considered every possibility
and taken steps early on for us!

75
00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:30.060
We already owe him so much...
but he kept saving us to the very end.

76
00:05:30.060 --> 00:05:34.110
If we did not take this opportunity,
it would bring us shame as samurai.

77
00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:39.740
All those years ago,
Lord Yasuie said the same to us.

78
00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:41.950
"Wano will have you...

79
00:05:41.950 --> 00:05:43.570
...as its guardians"!

80
00:05:45.890 --> 00:05:49.040
Yasuie sure was remarkable.

81
00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:56.210
We still face several challenges,
but with us all working together...

82
00:05:59.280 --> 00:06:03.890
our allied forces are growing
in number just as we had hoped!

83
00:06:04.210 --> 00:06:07.350
We still have no word on Denjiro,

84
00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:11.350
but we have gathered seven
of the Kozuki retainers!

85
00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:11.350
<b>Kanjuro
of the
Evening
Shower


Nine Red
Scabbards</b>

86
00:06:11.350 --> 00:06:13.310
<b>Kikunojo
 of the 
Lingering 
Snow


Nine Red 
Scabbards</b>

87
00:06:13.310 --> 00:06:15.230
<b>Kawamatsu
 "the Kappa"


Nine Red
 Scabbards</b>

88
00:06:15.230 --> 00:06:17.190
<b>Inuarashi


Nine Red 
Scabbards</b>

89
00:06:17.190 --> 00:06:19.110
<b>Ashura 
Doji


Nine Red 
Scabbards</b>

90
00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:21.070
<b>"Foxfire"
 Kin'emon


Nine Red 
Scabbards</b>

91
00:06:21.070 --> 00:06:22.780
<b>Raizo of the Mist

Nine Red Scabbards</b>

92
00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:28.490
This is huge. Our goal of having
5,000 soldiers at our backs is within sight.

93
00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:30.750
Yes, it's impressive!

94
00:06:32.200 --> 00:06:34.830
How long are we gonna sit here
flapping our jaws?!

95
00:06:35.070 --> 00:06:36.830
We're wasting time!

96
00:06:37.840 --> 00:06:42.550
Indeed. Let us start by going over the plan!

97
00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:46.640
It is imperative that we take Kaido and Orochi's heads

98
00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:51.100
so that we may avenge our late Lord Oden!

99
00:06:54.730 --> 00:06:57.490
Check it out!

100
00:06:58.300 --> 00:06:59.820
It just so happens...

101
00:07:02.450 --> 00:07:06.990
there are actually two ways to enter Wano.

102
00:07:07.550 --> 00:07:13.310
The first involves rolling the dice
on having carp pull your ship to the mainland.

103
00:07:14.590 --> 00:07:19.550
The second requires passing through
a waterfall into a cave.

104
00:07:21.280 --> 00:07:27.180
Naturally, no one can pass safely
without Kaido or Orochi's permission.

105
00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:31.310
<b>Mogura
Port</b>

106
00:07:27.750 --> 00:07:31.310
At the end of the cave lies Mogura Port.

107
00:07:34.540 --> 00:07:39.810
Its port has a gondola
that hoists sailors and cargo.

108
00:07:35.890 --> 00:07:38.560
<b>Mogura
Port</b>

109
00:07:40.040 --> 00:07:42.400
When they rise out of the end of the tunnel...

110
00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:47.230
<b>Flower
Capital Ringo</b>

111
00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:51.280
<b>Hakumai</b>

112
00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:47.440
<b>Kibi</b>

113
00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:47.360
<b>Kuri</b>

114
00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:47.780
<b>Udon</b>
<b>Onigashima</b>

115
00:07:46.980 --> 00:07:48.320
<b>Flower
Capital</b>

116
00:07:47.230 --> 00:07:47.900
<b>Ringo</b>

117
00:07:48.230 --> 00:07:51.280
they'll find themselves in Hakumai.

118
00:07:54.520 --> 00:07:56.330
Hello, Kaido?

119
00:07:57.020 --> 00:07:59.380
I've arrived in Hakumai.

120
00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:01.960
<b>Onigashima</b>

121
00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:05.340
Oh, you guys took the trouble
to come back for the party, too?

122
00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:09.590
Fo' shizzle!

123
00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:16.770
It's the annual Golden Festival!
I don't wanna be left out!

124
00:08:16.770 --> 00:08:19.400
This year's will knock your socks off!

125
00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:20.950
Can't wait!

126
00:08:20.950 --> 00:08:22.980
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

127
00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:25.150
It's gonna be fresh!

128
00:08:38.790 --> 00:08:41.570
Wh-Wh-What are they?!

129
00:08:43.210 --> 00:08:49.090
I-I-It's the Numbers from Onigashima!

130
00:08:49.760 --> 00:08:51.140
We gotta get outta here!

131
00:08:51.440 --> 00:08:53.030
They'll eat us!

132
00:08:57.240 --> 00:08:59.420
Word is the Numbers have returned.

133
00:08:59.420 --> 00:09:00.390
What?!

134
00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:05.150
I can't stand how messy
they get when they drink!

135
00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:09.650
On the night of the Fire Festival,
we'll have the greatest party ever!

136
00:09:09.990 --> 00:09:12.530
Yep! It'll mark a new anniversary!

137
00:09:15.500 --> 00:09:19.500
What's this? You two go from being
mortal enemies to best friends?

138
00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:25.880
Hey, listen up, gents!

139
00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:26.590
What is it?

140
00:09:27.050 --> 00:09:29.840
The Beast Pirates...

141
00:09:29.840 --> 00:09:32.720
...and the Big Mom Pirates...

142
00:09:33.450 --> 00:09:34.600
Let me stand up.

143
00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:36.680
...have decided...

144
00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:38.390
...to enter into...

145
00:09:38.390 --> 00:09:40.310
– ...an alliance!
– ...an alliance!

146
00:09:41.670 --> 00:09:42.190
What?

147
00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:47.570
We'll join forces
and conquer the world first!

148
00:09:47.570 --> 00:09:51.110
Then we can go back to killing each other!

149
00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:59.040
Whaaat?!

150
00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:01.500
<b>Amigasa
 Village


Kuri,
Wano</b>

151
00:10:05.820 --> 00:10:10.050
Is it really... truly... true?!

152
00:10:10.520 --> 00:10:11.630
Yes, it is true.

153
00:10:11.930 --> 00:10:14.930
Princess Hiyori lives?!

154
00:10:15.750 --> 00:10:18.680
Yes. She does.

155
00:10:21.790 --> 00:10:25.520
I am worried sick about Otoko...

156
00:10:26.260 --> 00:10:29.400
but still... Kawamatsu...

157
00:10:29.930 --> 00:10:33.280
I will not go to see everyone at this moment.

158
00:10:33.680 --> 00:10:37.410
Those going into battle
must stay their emotions.

159
00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:47.880
Please just find a way
to come together and save Wano.

160
00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:52.790
Y-Your Highness! Please stop that
at once! Raise your head!

161
00:10:58.600 --> 00:11:02.770
That mischievous little devil
said something so polite?!

162
00:11:03.690 --> 00:11:05.690
How she has grown!

163
00:11:06.170 --> 00:11:12.230
Kawamatsu, I imagined the worst
after you mentioned getting captured,

164
00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:16.130
so I was paralyzed in my asking about her!

165
00:11:16.810 --> 00:11:19.760
Where is she?! Does she need protection?!

166
00:11:19.760 --> 00:11:23.200
Do not worry. She is in a secure location.

167
00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:26.580
What great news!

168
00:11:27.030 --> 00:11:29.180
It is truly incredible!

169
00:11:33.090 --> 00:11:35.020
She is alive...

170
00:11:41.390 --> 00:11:43.150
Big Brother!

171
00:11:43.150 --> 00:11:45.120
Oh, Hiyori!

172
00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:47.440
Dropkick!

173
00:11:52.540 --> 00:11:53.630
Hiyori...

174
00:11:54.710 --> 00:11:56.350
Zorojuro!

175
00:11:57.220 --> 00:11:59.070
You were the one who saved her?

176
00:11:59.880 --> 00:12:01.380
I thank you!

177
00:12:01.380 --> 00:12:04.910
Hiyori comes off as strong, but it is just a front.

178
00:12:04.910 --> 00:12:08.080
She also troubles everyone with all her crying.

179
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:08.920
Hey, Momo.

180
00:12:08.920 --> 00:12:11.500
Aren't your memories of her a bit outdated?

181
00:12:12.200 --> 00:12:15.340
Now she's eighteen years older than you.

182
00:12:15.340 --> 00:12:15.970
Huh?!

183
00:12:20.330 --> 00:12:21.890
Dropkick!

184
00:12:23.690 --> 00:12:28.480
A dropkick from someone
eighteen years older?! That would hurt...

185
00:12:29.610 --> 00:12:32.400
You're telling me that
the beauty I saw with you...

186
00:12:32.810 --> 00:12:35.190
is Momonosuke's little sister?!

187
00:12:38.840 --> 00:12:40.240
Wh-What are you...?

188
00:12:44.070 --> 00:12:47.130
My dear Momonosuke!

189
00:12:47.130 --> 00:12:50.010
Is there anything I can get you?

190
00:12:50.010 --> 00:12:52.250
Don't brownnose her brother, idiot.

191
00:12:52.700 --> 00:12:56.920
Sir Sangoro, stop that tomfoolery already.

192
00:12:57.460 --> 00:13:01.050
Kawamatsu! They are ready!

193
00:13:01.620 --> 00:13:04.350
Are you sure about this?

194
00:13:04.840 --> 00:13:08.390
Yes. We have made our decision.

195
00:13:09.130 --> 00:13:11.660
Sir Hitetsu, take this first.

196
00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:17.230
This is Kitetsu II, which had been
confiscated from Luffytaro at Udon.

197
00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:20.900
Ah, thank you. He took it
without my permission.

198
00:13:22.370 --> 00:13:23.320
Kitetsu...

199
00:13:26.440 --> 00:13:28.410
I knew it was a named blade.

200
00:13:29.680 --> 00:13:33.420
Hark! My name is Tenguyama Hitetsu!

201
00:13:33.830 --> 00:13:36.610
I am a swordsmith of Wano!

202
00:13:37.670 --> 00:13:39.170
For two decades,

203
00:13:39.170 --> 00:13:47.510
I have awaited the day that I can deliver
these swords to Lord Momonosuke and Lady Hiyori.

204
00:13:54.860 --> 00:13:57.570
These were Lord Oden's precious blades:

205
00:13:57.990 --> 00:14:01.700
Ame no Habakiri, the heaven splitter,

206
00:14:02.040 --> 00:14:06.310
and Enma, which can cut
the bottom of hell itself!

207
00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:13.130
Both are counted among the twenty-one
great grade swords, alongside Shusui.

208
00:14:14.260 --> 00:14:18.960
Lord Momonosuke, what would you
like to do with my masterpiece?

209
00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:21.510
N-No, I am still not...

210
00:14:21.890 --> 00:14:27.930
It is not that I am afraid to wield it,
but please safekeep it for me a bit longer.

211
00:14:28.340 --> 00:14:32.380
And now, the sword called
Enma belongs to you!

212
00:14:33.460 --> 00:14:38.700
I must first inform you that only one man in this country was able to handle Enma:

213
00:14:38.700 --> 00:14:42.360
Kozuki Oden, and no one before or since!

214
00:14:53.790 --> 00:14:58.510
Go on and try to cut down one of those trees.

215
00:15:04.950 --> 00:15:05.930
Sir Zoro.

216
00:15:06.660 --> 00:15:12.560
I say this with the utmost kindness,
but if I were you, I would refuse that blade.

217
00:15:33.180 --> 00:15:34.750
He cut off the whole cliff!

218
00:15:47.410 --> 00:15:49.840
Zorojuro, your arm!

219
00:15:56.400 --> 00:15:57.440
Why you...!

220
00:16:00.410 --> 00:16:01.320
Give it back!

221
00:16:18.550 --> 00:16:24.060
It siphons the wielder's ryuo as it pleases
and cuts more than is necessary.

222
00:16:25.370 --> 00:16:30.220
An average swordsman would have turned
bone dry and fallen over.

223
00:16:30.510 --> 00:16:32.100
Magnificent!

224
00:16:32.500 --> 00:16:35.600
What do you think?
Shall I give you a different sword?

225
00:16:38.610 --> 00:16:41.620
No, I'll keep this one.

226
00:16:41.620 --> 00:16:43.180
Enma, huh?

227
00:16:44.130 --> 00:16:46.110
Once I get used to this thing...

228
00:16:46.790 --> 00:16:51.400
I'll become even stronger, won't I?

229
00:16:55.570 --> 00:16:57.120
What a character!

230
00:17:01.690 --> 00:17:06.550
Work your asses off! Time is running out!

231
00:17:06.550 --> 00:17:18.020
<b>Three

Days

Until

the Raid</b>

232
00:17:06.810 --> 00:17:10.080
They need to be strong enough
to carry 100,000 people!

233
00:17:10.080 --> 00:17:11.930
There won't be that many!

234
00:17:11.930 --> 00:17:15.530
Moron! We want to prep for
as many allies as possible!

235
00:17:15.530 --> 00:17:18.020
Let's bet on it! How many will come?!

236
00:17:19.310 --> 00:17:22.560
Lady Orobi, what is the size
of the enemy's military force?

237
00:17:23.320 --> 00:17:25.320
Based on the information I gathered...

238
00:17:26.120 --> 00:17:30.070
the Beast Pirates have about 20,000 troops.

239
00:17:30.570 --> 00:17:34.810
Shogun Orochi is expected to be
accompanied by 10,000 men.

240
00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:40.410
In short, there will be 30,000
enemies on Onigashima that day.

241
00:17:40.730 --> 00:17:45.710
There are no commoners to get in the way,
so they have a geographical advantage.

242
00:17:45.710 --> 00:17:47.670
Even with the mansion's blueprints.

243
00:17:48.340 --> 00:17:52.340
In contrast, we have roughly 4,000 warriors.

244
00:17:52.980 --> 00:17:57.510
It may not be a full-scale war,
but they still have overwhelming numbers.

245
00:17:58.070 --> 00:18:02.020
Nevertheless, our raid plan
is currently our only option!

246
00:18:02.570 --> 00:18:04.270
We must execute it!

247
00:18:04.270 --> 00:18:06.060
Gear Fourth...

248
00:18:13.570 --> 00:18:15.240
Boundman!

249
00:18:18.580 --> 00:18:20.370
<b>Prisoner
 Mining
 Camp

Udon</b>

250
00:18:21.580 --> 00:18:24.250
King Kong Gun!

251
00:18:36.420 --> 00:18:38.360
No good enough.

252
00:18:38.360 --> 00:18:40.930
Yes, it uses too much force.

253
00:18:41.210 --> 00:18:42.930
– What?! It wasn't good enough?!
– What?! It wasn't good enough?!

254
00:18:57.870 --> 00:19:00.370
Keep still!

255
00:19:08.760 --> 00:19:11.680
Momo, is that it for your training?

256
00:19:13.720 --> 00:19:19.510
Speaking of training, do you remember
how you taught me the word "SNATCH"?

257
00:19:19.510 --> 00:19:20.890
Hm? Yeah.

258
00:19:22.010 --> 00:19:25.400
You said it's a lucky word that lifts your spirit.

259
00:19:25.400 --> 00:19:26.190
Right.

260
00:19:26.590 --> 00:19:30.350
But Okiku told me not to say it.

261
00:19:30.350 --> 00:19:35.730
An old man from my village taught it to me a long
time ago, but I've never once said it myself.

262
00:19:35.730 --> 00:19:36.740
What?!

263
00:19:38.750 --> 00:19:42.330
Hey! Master!

264
00:19:39.200 --> 00:19:42.330
<b>Two Days

Until

the Raid</b>

265
00:19:43.040 --> 00:19:44.560
Otama!

266
00:19:45.550 --> 00:19:47.790
You had me so worried!

267
00:19:47.790 --> 00:19:49.630
Chopper! Luffy!

268
00:19:50.060 --> 00:19:50.710
Nami!

269
00:19:59.050 --> 00:20:00.600
This is Kin'emon speaking.

270
00:20:00.970 --> 00:20:02.310
Lord Kin'emon.

271
00:20:03.540 --> 00:20:08.060
Kibi, Hakumai, Ringo, and Udon

272
00:20:08.490 --> 00:20:11.400
have brought an additional 200 troops!

273
00:20:13.780 --> 00:20:14.990
Are you serious?!

274
00:20:18.860 --> 00:20:20.760
Hooray!

275
00:20:20.760 --> 00:20:23.590
That brings our force to 4,200 warriors!

276
00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:27.250
We have not heard from Sir Law though...

277
00:20:28.190 --> 00:20:30.630
Does it matter whether or not he calls in?

278
00:20:30.630 --> 00:20:33.130
Yeah, he's really strong!

279
00:20:36.220 --> 00:20:39.760
Big Bro trained so much
that he won't wake up.

280
00:20:45.410 --> 00:20:46.430
Hey, guard!

281
00:20:47.600 --> 00:20:50.150
It's almost the festival. We want to attend!

282
00:20:50.510 --> 00:20:52.230
No way! Pipe down now!

283
00:20:52.590 --> 00:20:55.530
Damn it! This is our last chance!

284
00:20:55.530 --> 00:20:58.300
The others will be risking their lives to fight!

285
00:20:59.110 --> 00:21:02.070
<b>Rasetsu 
Prison

Flower
 Capital</b>

286
00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:02.070
I'm sorry for those jailed in the capital,

287
00:21:02.070 --> 00:21:05.920
but there's nothing we can do for them.

288
00:21:05.920 --> 00:21:09.290
They even jailed any
family members who protested.

289
00:21:09.290 --> 00:21:13.630
Our most strapping samurai are among them...

290
00:21:14.160 --> 00:21:15.920
but we have no more time.

291
00:21:18.080 --> 00:21:21.720
Everyone! Thank you for all your efforts!

292
00:21:22.310 --> 00:21:26.010
Use the remaining time to get
into position and prepare.

293
00:21:26.370 --> 00:21:27.220
Understood!

294
00:21:27.660 --> 00:21:31.100
See you at the rendezvous port!

295
00:21:35.440 --> 00:21:39.820
<b>One Day

Until

the Raid</b>

296
00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:38.710
I braided one for everyone!

297
00:21:38.710 --> 00:21:39.820
We are grateful.

298
00:21:41.370 --> 00:21:45.100
Sir Luffy... we will go on ahead.

299
00:21:45.650 --> 00:21:47.530
We must be the first to arrive.

300
00:21:47.530 --> 00:21:48.080
Okay!

301
00:21:48.510 --> 00:21:52.360
Our ship, the Sunny, is docked here.

302
00:21:52.360 --> 00:21:53.790
Don't get found out!

303
00:21:53.790 --> 00:21:57.900
Not on your life! We keep a tight ship.

304
00:22:01.240 --> 00:22:03.590
We are counting on you all.

305
00:22:04.070 --> 00:22:06.970
Sure thing. Leave it to us!

306
00:22:07.360 --> 00:22:08.850
See you at the port!

307
00:22:09.820 --> 00:22:10.650
Yeah!

308
00:22:24.660 --> 00:22:28.540
In this land of countless smokestacks,

309
00:22:30.980 --> 00:22:35.010
the number of unhappy
laborers is even greater.

310
00:22:35.520 --> 00:22:37.110
Do you think it's true?

311
00:22:37.110 --> 00:22:38.510
What?

312
00:22:38.510 --> 00:22:39.630
Lord Yasuie...

313
00:22:40.070 --> 00:22:43.220
...was covering for the Nine Red
Scabbards! Did you hear?

314
00:22:43.220 --> 00:22:43.880
What?

315
00:22:43.880 --> 00:22:45.050
They say that flyer...

316
00:22:45.540 --> 00:22:51.140
...was not a prank by Lord Yasuie,
rather it was the signal for the raid.

317
00:22:51.500 --> 00:22:54.600
Don't feed me any of your wild dreams.

318
00:22:54.600 --> 00:22:58.730
Remember what happened to
the Kozuki Clan twenty years ago.

319
00:22:59.240 --> 00:23:03.730
Even if Kin'emon and the rest are still alive...

320
00:23:06.940 --> 00:23:09.910
their spirits must have been broken.

321
00:23:10.440 --> 00:23:14.290
They won't rise up again!

322
00:23:15.110 --> 00:23:17.420
This country is so isolated.

323
00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:20.050
No one's coming to help!

324
00:23:20.600 --> 00:23:26.130
And besides, no one can stand up to Kaido!

325
00:23:27.120 --> 00:23:29.760
Setting out in silence are...

326
00:23:29.760 --> 00:23:35.310
seven Red Scabbard samurai, one ninja,
and one person of great importance.

327
00:23:35.610 --> 00:23:41.150
They tread on parched land that
crunches like frost in winter.

328
00:23:43.050 --> 00:23:45.970
The sun shines high up in the sky.

329
00:23:46.490 --> 00:23:48.130
There are some dark clouds...

330
00:23:49.130 --> 00:23:54.080
but the shadows of the nine,
who indeed are not ghosts...

331
00:23:54.500 --> 00:23:57.870
and who intend to avenge their
lord after two decades...

332
00:23:57.870 --> 00:24:00.880
are clearly cast upon the ground.

333
00:24:01.610 --> 00:24:04.880
After we've won, let's erect nicer headstones.

334
00:24:03.670 --> 00:24:06.420
<b>Yasuie</b>

335
00:24:08.380 --> 00:24:10.220
<b>Pedro</b>

336
00:24:16.230 --> 00:24:18.760
That Kitetsu looks different now.

337
00:24:20.050 --> 00:24:23.150
It seems to have found a good owner.

338
00:24:24.270 --> 00:24:28.530
That Kitetsu III of yours is my craft.

339
00:24:28.940 --> 00:24:30.330
Really?!

340
00:24:31.020 --> 00:24:32.200
Boy.

341
00:24:32.200 --> 00:24:37.610
Lady Hiyori gifted Enma to you, which I would wager
feels oddly comfortable in your hand, correct?

342
00:24:38.760 --> 00:24:41.040
It is the same as any cursed sword.

343
00:24:41.550 --> 00:24:44.310
The weak cannot handle them.

344
00:24:44.310 --> 00:24:48.930
But the main reason it fits so comfortably
in your hand is, by some twist of fate...

345
00:24:49.350 --> 00:24:54.060
because Wado Ichimonji and Enma
were crafted by the same person!

346
00:24:55.900 --> 00:24:59.580
The master swordsmith Shimotsuki Kozaburo.

347
00:24:59.580 --> 00:25:05.030
That man illegally emigrated
from Wano more than fifty years ago.

348
00:25:05.560 --> 00:25:11.340
Perhaps Lady Hiyori gave you the memento from
her father because she recognized that sword.

349
00:25:13.950 --> 00:25:17.080
Enma has not yet been forged
into a black blade!

350
00:25:17.780 --> 00:25:20.960
Its rank can be raised depending on you.

351
00:25:22.620 --> 00:25:24.830
Then that's just what I'll do!

352
00:25:27.020 --> 00:25:28.770
Udon is secure?!

353
00:25:28.770 --> 00:25:30.740
Yes, sir. No problems here.

354
00:25:30.740 --> 00:25:32.640
Huh, I must have been misinformed!

355
00:25:33.000 --> 00:25:37.110
Yes, sir. Nothing has changed here in Udon.

356
00:25:37.110 --> 00:25:40.440
We continue to guard the prisoners.

357
00:25:40.710 --> 00:25:41.610
Over and out.

358
00:25:42.630 --> 00:25:45.840
I don't trust him acting so strange!

359
00:25:46.490 --> 00:25:51.070
But as long as I have this information,
it's more than enough.

360
00:25:46.860 --> 00:25:51.070
<b>Moved from Habu Port to Tokage Port.
Kozuki Hiyori Lives
Northern Region</b>

361
00:25:51.670 --> 00:25:59.570
"Moved from Habu Port to Tokage Port.
Kozuki Hiyori lives. Northern Region," huh?

362
00:26:40.970 --> 00:26:43.160
Watch out, Kaido!

363
00:26:45.770 --> 00:26:48.250
Gather 'round!

364
00:26:49.320 --> 00:26:52.840
Fair weather graces the Flower Capital
as the cherry blossoms fall.

365
00:26:53.780 --> 00:26:56.010
The day of the Fire Festival has arrived!

366
00:26:56.780 --> 00:27:03.440
Meanwhile, in the shadows looms a battle
that would sway even the fate of the world!

367
00:27:08.350 --> 00:27:11.230
<b>Act 2</b>
<b>FIN</b>
<b>Wano</b>
